The paper focuses on object tracking and classification using event-based cameras and neuromorphic computing, which are topics commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use case of surveillance applications suggests that the paper may also fall under robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning and classification, which are topics commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
